Package prototype

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Board
    The Board class is used to create the board and hold the logic that is used to play checkers.
    Checkers
    Checkers class, this is where the main method is and how the entire program starts.
    CheckersAI
    The AI class is used when a player wants to play against the computer.
    CheckersGUI
    This class holds the JFrame initilization, creates and fills the JPanels-- including the Checkers Panel.
    CheckersPanel
    This class is the panel in which most of the graphical work is done.
    Game
    This holds the logic behind the game, for example the button Logic, if the game is running, and the current player.
    Player
    The Player class defines field variables that contain information about a player.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ColorStatus
    Enumerator for all the state that the board can have.
    GameMode
    Enumerator for the game modes There are 3 modes: free mode: is where there is no time limits imposed on the users.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    OutOfBoundsException
    This class is called if the user tries to move off the board.
